pr_review_comment_body:
@cschneid - I believe we have a one-to-one match between config settings keys and env vars in all of our agents. This is nice. In this case, it looks like the config setting is `git_sha` and the env var is `SCOUT_REVISION_SHA`. 

I'd suggest we change the config to `revision_sha`. We use this naming for Ruby.

/cc @dlanderson

Prefer the `}` dedent to align with it's start:

```python
        resource = Resource(
            type='gae_app',
            labels={
                'module_id': 'default',
                'version_id': 'test',
            },
        )
```
